@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>@ViewData["Title"]</title>
</head>
<body>

    <h1>Privacy Statement for Camp Password Manager - Enterprise</h1>

    <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> 10/07/2024</p>

    <h2>Introduction</h2>
    <p>Welcome to Camp Password Manager - Enterprise. We prioritize your privacy and are committed to safeguarding your personal information. This Privacy Statement outlines how we collect, use, and protect your data when you use our application.</p>

    <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Personal Information:</strong> We collect your email address, display name, given name, and surname when you create an account or use our services.</li>
        <li><strong>Stored Data:</strong> All information stored within Camp Password Manager - Enterprise, including passwords and sensitive data, is encrypted and protected using advanced security measures.</li>
        <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> We minimally collect data, primarily tracking PIN retry attempts to enhance security and verification mechanisms.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>We use your information to provide, maintain, and improve our services, ensuring a seamless user experience. Additionally, we enhance application security to protect against unauthorized access and potential threats. We may also use your contact information to provide updates, security alerts, and relevant service communications.</p>

    <h2>Least Privilege</h2>
    <p>Application functionalities avoid dependence on single providers, accommodating mixed Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) setups. Session duration adjustments are facilitated, defaulting to 60 minutes per Access Key.</p>

    <h2>Information Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
    <p>We do not sell, trade, or transfer your personal information to external parties, except in cases with your consent or legal obligations.</p>

    <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>We partner with reputable third-party service providers to enhance our offerings. These services are strictly utilized to deliver specific functionalities and do not access customer data.</p>

    <h2>Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
    <p>Our application utilizes native cloud computing without local caching, ensuring data is securely stored in the cloud. We adhere to the best practices of frameworks like .NET and open operating systems.</p>

    <h2>International Data Transfers</h2>
    <p>Data is stored in static storage configurations, minimizing scalability while ensuring phishing-resistant security measures. Our architecture supports secure data handling and storage, facilitating scalable and secure password management.</p>

    <h2>Children’s Privacy</h2>
    <p>Our services are intended for users aged 12 and older. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 12.</p>

    <h2>Data Retention</h2>
    <p>Personal data is retained for operational and legal compliance purposes. We implement a mechanism for permanent deletion, executed after a 30-day retention period.</p>

    <h2>Data Breach Notification</h2>
    <p>In the event of a data breach compromising personal information, we promptly notify affected users and relevant authorities.</p>

    <h2>User Consent</h2>
    <p>Your consent is obtained for data collection and processing, adhering to legal requirements. Withdrawal of consent is honored, subject to applicable laws and contractual obligations.</p>

    <h2>Microsoft Edge Integration</h2>
    <p>Camp Password Manager - Enterprise works well with Microsoft Edge. The application can target Microsoft Edge and will minimize the browser once authenticated.</p>

    <h2>Changes to This Privacy Statement</h2>
    <p>Updates to this Privacy Statement are posted on our platform. Significant changes prompt direct communication through the application or email.</p>

    <h2>Contact Us</h2>
    <p>For inquiries about our Privacy Statement or data handling practices, contact us at:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Email: <a href="mailto:croftteams@camppasswordmanager.com">croftteams@camppasswordmanager.com</a></li>
    </ul>

    <p>Thank you for choosing Camp Password Manager - Enterprise. We prioritize your privacy and security.</p>

</body>
</html>
